    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. I think I'll emphasize that in class. One more thing—since some people argue that substantive due process is basically just judges making up rights that aren't actually in the Constitution, how should I explain to my students that this view is just an attempt to roll back progress and ignore the evolving nature of justice?",
